ns, Charles, Clement and John.<ref name=\"get to know\">{{cite web|title=Get to know the candidates in the 5th District|url=http://www2.dailyprogress.com/m/news/2010/oct/23/get-know-candidates-5th-district-ar-582837/|publisher=''The Daily Progress''|accessdate=2011-08-20|date=2010-10-23}}</ref>  Hurt is a member of Chatham Presbyterian Church and Chatham Rotary Club. Also, he is a member of the Board of Directors of the New College Institute, the Virginia Bar Association\u2019s Board of Governors, the Hampden-Sydney Wilson Center Advisory Board, the John Marshall Foundation Board, the Board of Directors of Roman Eagle Nursing Home and the board of directors of the W. E. Skelton 4-H Conference Center at [[Smith Mountain Lake]].<ref name=\"hopes to\">{{cite web|last=Riddle|first=Sonny|title=Hurt hopes to unseat Perriello for seat in Washington|url=http://www.gazettevirginian.com/index.php/news/34-news/1973-hurt-hopes-to-unseat-perriello-for-seat-in-washington|publisher=''The Gazette-Virginian''|accessdate=2011-08-20|date=2010-11-01}}</ref> His brother, Charles Hurt, is a journalist and political columnist for the ''[[The Washington Times|Washington Times]]''.<ref name=\"hosted AP\">{{cite news| title =Robert Hurt Bio| agency =Associated Press| url =http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/external/pre-election/bios/45695.html?SITE=WSJVTVELN&SECTION=POLITICS&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT| accessdate =2010-12-20 }}</ref><ref name=\"Washington Times\">{{cite news| title =Staff Members\\Charles Hurt| newspaper =Washington Times| url =http://www.washingtontimes.com/staff/charles-hurt/| accessdate =2014-10-14 }}</ref> Hurt gave the [[commencement address]] at [[Piedmont Virginia Community College]] in May 2011.<ref name=\"gives speech\">{{cite web|last=Jaglois|first=Jessica|title=Hurt Gives Speech at PVCC Graduation; Talks Jobs, Gas Prices|url=http://www.newsplex.com/home/headlines/Hurt_Gives_Speech_at_PVCC_Graduation_Talks_Jobs_Gas_Prices_121816994.html|publisher=[[WCAV]]|accessdate=2011-08-20|date=2011-05-13}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=35em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Robert Hurt}}\n*[http://hurt.house.gov/ Congressman Robert Hurt] official U.S. House site\n*[http://www.roberthurtforcongress.com/ Robert Hurt for Congress] \n*{{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Virginia/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Robert_Hurt_%5BR-5%5D|Robert Hurt}}\n*{{CongLinks | congbio = H001060 | ballot = Robert_Hurt | nndb = 843/000265048 | votesmart = 50895 | govtrack = 412484 | opencong = 412484 | rollcall = 31509 | politifact = robert-hurt | fec = H0VA05095 | opensecrets = N00031265 | assets = robert-hurt | legistorm = 2804/Rep_Robert_Hurt_VA.html | followthemoney = 7166 | ontheissues = VA/Robert_Hurt.htm | congress = robert-hurt/2069 | worldcat = | c-span = roberthurt | imdb = 4151421 | bloomberg = | nyt = | washpo = gIQAfrpVKP }}\n*[http://www.vpap.org/candidates/profile/home/24590 Profile] from ''Virginia Public Access Project''\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{USRepSuccessionBox\n|state=Virginia\n|district=5\n|before=[[Tom Perriello]]\n|after=Incumbent|years=January 3, 2011 &ndash; present}}\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Randy Hultgren]]<br><small>R-[[Illinois]]</small>}}\n{{s-ttl|title=''[[List of current members of the United States House of Representatives by seniority|United States Representatives by seniority]]''|years=307th}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bill Johnson (Ohio politician)|Bill Johnson]]<br><small>R-[[Ohio]]</small>}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{VA-FedRep}}\n\n{{Persondata\n| NAME              =Hurt, Robert\n| ALTERNATIVE NAMES =\n| SHORT DESCRIPTION =Virginia Politician\n| DATE OF BIRTH     =1969-06-16\n| PLACE OF BIRTH    = Virginia, United States\n| DATE OF DEATH     =\n| PLACE OF DEATH    =\n}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hurt, Robert}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from New York City]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Ca